.Dd June 22, 2026
.Dt APPLE_SMC 4
.Os
.Sh NAME
.Nm apple_smc
.Nd Apple System Management Controller driver
.Sh SYNOPSIS
To compile this driver into the kernel,
place the following line in your
kernel configuration file:
.Bd -ragged -offset indent
.Cd "device apple_smc"
.Ed
.Pp
Alternatively, to load the driver as a
module at boot time, place the following line in
.Xr loader.conf 5 :
.Bd -literal -offset indent
apple_smc_load="YES"
.Ed
.Sh DESCRIPTION
The
.Nm
driver provides support for the System Management Controller (SMC) found
in Apple Macintosh computers.
The SMC manages fans, temperature sensors, keyboard backlight,
ambient light sensors, the Sudden Motion Sensor (SMS), and various
system state keys.
.Pp
The driver supports two hardware backends:
.Bl -bullet -offset indent
.It
ISA I/O port (port 0x300) on Intel Macs through iMac13,x.
.It
MMIO register window on newer Intel Macs (iMac14,x and later),
including those with an Apple T2 security chip.
.El
.Pp
The MMIO backend is probed first.
If a memory-mapped BAR is present and responds, the driver uses MMIO;
otherwise it falls back to ISA port I/O.
T2 Macs are identified by an
.Va RGEN
key value of 3.
.Pp
All sensor values and controls are exposed through the
.Xr sysctl 8
interface under
.Va dev.apple_smc.0 .
.Sh SYSCTL VARIABLES
.Ss Fan Controls
Each fan is exposed under
.Va dev.apple_smc.0.fan.<N>
where
.Aq N
is the fan number starting from 0.
.Bl -tag -width indent
.It Va dev.apple_smc.0.fan.<N>.id
.Pq read-only
Fan model identification string.
.It Va dev.apple_smc.0.fan.<N>.speed
.Pq read-only
Current fan speed in RPM.
.It Va dev.apple_smc.0.fan.<N>.safespeed
.Pq read-only
Fan safe speed in RPM.
Only present if the hardware reports a safe speed key.
.It Va dev.apple_smc.0.fan.<N>.minspeed
Minimum fan speed in RPM.
.It Va dev.apple_smc.0.fan.<N>.maxspeed
Maximum fan speed in RPM.
.It Va dev.apple_smc.0.fan.<N>.targetspeed
Target fan speed in RPM.
.It Va dev.apple_smc.0.fan.<N>.manual
Fan manual mode.
Set to 1 to disable automatic fan control, 0 to re-enable it.
On T2 Macs this uses the per-fan
.Va F<N>Md
key; on older Macs it uses the global
.Va FS!\&
bitmask.
.El
.Ss Temperature Sensors
Temperature sensors are auto-detected at attach time by scanning the
SMC key namespace for keys in the
.Ql T
range with
.Va sp78
type (signed 8.8 fixed-point, millidegrees Celsius).
.Pp
Sensors whose probe read returns a value below \-10000 millidegrees
are classified as Intel DTS (distance-to-Tj,max) sensors and placed
under a separate
.Va dts
subtree.
The sysctl handler converts DTS readings to absolute temperature using
the Tj,max value read from MSR 0x1A2 at attach time.
Sensors returning \-120000 or below are treated as disconnected and
are not registered.
.Bl -tag -width indent
.It Va dev.apple_smc.0.temp.<KEY>
.Pq read-only
Absolute temperature in millidegrees Celsius.
.Aq KEY
is the 4-character SMC key name, e.g.\&
.Ql TC0D
for CPU die temperature.
.It Va dev.apple_smc.0.temp.dts.<KEY>
.Pq read-only
DTS sensor converted to absolute temperature.
.El
.Ss Voltage, Current, and Power Sensors
Voltage, current, and power sensors are auto-detected by scanning the
.Ql V ,
.Ql I ,
and
.Ql P
key ranges respectively.
Values are reported in millivolts, milliamps, or milliwatts.
.Bl -tag -width indent
.It Va dev.apple_smc.0.voltage.<KEY>
.Pq read-only
Voltage in millivolts.
.It Va dev.apple_smc.0.current.<KEY>
.Pq read-only
Current in milliamps.
.It Va dev.apple_smc.0.power.<KEY>
.Pq read-only
Power in milliwatts.
.El
.Ss Ambient Light Sensors
.Bl -tag -width indent
.It Va dev.apple_smc.0.ambient.<KEY>
.Pq read-only
Ambient light sensor reading.
Keys are typically
.Ql ALV0 ,
.Ql ALV1 ,
etc.
.El
.Ss Keyboard Backlight
.Bl -tag -width indent
.It Va dev.apple_smc.0.light.left
.Pq read-only
Left ambient light sensor value used for keyboard backlight.
On newer models with 10-byte payloads, a dedicated decoder is used.
.It Va dev.apple_smc.0.light.right
.Pq read-only
Right ambient light sensor value.
Only present on models with a separate right sensor and 6-byte payloads.
.It Va dev.apple_smc.0.light.control
Keyboard backlight brightness, 0 (off) to 255 (maximum).
The value is cached and restored on resume from suspend.
.El
.Ss Sudden Motion Sensor (SMS)
The SMS provides three-axis accelerometer data.
It is only present on MacBook and MacBook Pro models with
a built-in hard disk motion sensor.
.Pp
SMS events are delivered to
.Xr devd 8
with system
.Ql ACPI ,
subsystem
.Ql apple_smc ,
and type
.Ql SMS .
The notify value encodes the event type:
0 = shock, 1 = high acceleration, 2 = free fall.
.Bl -tag -width indent
.It Va dev.apple_smc.0.sms.x
.Pq read-only
Accelerometer X axis value.
.It Va dev.apple_smc.0.sms.y
.Pq read-only
Accelerometer Y axis value.
.It Va dev.apple_smc.0.sms.z
.Pq read-only
Accelerometer Z axis value.
.El
.Ss System State
These sysctls are only present if the corresponding SMC key exists
on the hardware.
.Bl -tag -width indent
.It Va dev.apple_smc.0.system.shutdown_cause
.Pq read-only
Last shutdown cause as reported by the
.Va MSSD
key, decoded to a human-readable string where known
.Pq e.g.\& Dq 5 (good-shutdown) .
.It Va dev.apple_smc.0.system.sleep_cause
.Pq read-only
Last sleep cause
.Pq Va MSSP .
.It Va dev.apple_smc.0.system.thermal_status
.Pq read-only
Thermal subsystem alert flags
.Pq Va MSAL .
Decoded bits include TSS, thermal validity, calibration validity,
PROCHOT assertion, and power limits.
.It Va dev.apple_smc.0.system.time_of_day
.Pq read-only
SMC clock: seconds since midnight
.Pq Va CLKT .
.It Va dev.apple_smc.0.system.power_state
.Pq read-only
SMC power state index
.Pq Va MSPS .
.It Va dev.apple_smc.0.system.board_id
.Pq read-only
Apple board codename, e.g.\&
.Ql Mac-27ADBB7B4CEE8E61
.Pq Va RPlt .
.It Va dev.apple_smc.0.system.chip_gen
.Pq read-only
Apple chip generation; a value of 3 indicates a T2 coprocessor
.Pq Va RGEN .
.El
.Ss Battery Charge Limit (T2 only)
.Bl -tag -width indent
.It Va dev.apple_smc.0.battery_charge_limit
Battery charge limit percentage, 0 to 100
.Pq Va BCLM .
Only present on T2 Macs.
.El
.Ss Auto Power-On
.Bl -tag -width indent
.It Va dev.apple_smc.0.auto_poweron
Auto power-on after AC power loss.
Set to 1 to enable, 0 to disable
.Pq Va AUPO .
.El
.Ss Debug Interface
When the kernel is compiled with
.Dv APPLE_SMC_DEBUG ,
a raw key access interface is available under
.Va dev.apple_smc.0.raw :
.Bl -tag -width indent
.It Va dev.apple_smc.0.raw.key
Write a 4-character SMC key name to select it.
.It Va dev.apple_smc.0.raw.value
Read or write the selected key's value as a hexadecimal string.
.It Va dev.apple_smc.0.raw.len
.Pq read-only
Length of the selected key's value in bytes.
.It Va dev.apple_smc.0.raw.type
.Pq read-only
4-character type code of the selected key.
.El
.Sh HARDWARE
The
.Nm
driver supports any Intel Mac with ACPI device
.Ql APP0001 .
.Sh EXAMPLES
Read the CPU die temperature:
.Bd -literal -offset indent
sysctl dev.apple_smc.0.temp.TC0D
.Ed
.Pp
Set fan 0 to manual mode at 2000 RPM:
.Bd -literal -offset indent
sysctl dev.apple_smc.0.fan.0.manual=1
sysctl dev.apple_smc.0.fan.0.targetspeed=2000
.Ed
.Pp
Check the last shutdown cause:
.Bd -literal -offset indent
sysctl dev.apple_smc.0.system.shutdown_cause
.Ed
.Pp
Limit battery charge to 80% on a T2 Mac:
.Bd -literal -offset indent
sysctl dev.apple_smc.0.battery_charge_limit=80
.Ed
.Sh SEE ALSO
.Xr acpi 4 ,
.Xr apple_fw 4 ,
.Xr sysctl.conf 5 ,
.Xr devd 8 ,
.Xr sysctl 8
